Installation
============

If you're using maven, simply add the following dependency to your project:


    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.mongojack</groupId>
        <artifactId>mongojack</artifactId>
        <version>${siteProjectVersion}</version>
    </dependency>

Gradle Groovy DSL:

    implementation 'org.mongojack:mongojack:${siteProjectVersion}'

Gradle Kotlin DSL:

    implementation("org.mongojack:mongojack:${siteProjectVersion}")


You can download the dependency directly from here:

http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/mongojack/mongojack/${siteProjectVersion}/mongojack-${siteProjectVersion}.jar

Source code can be obtained from the [GitHub project](https://github.com/mongojack/mongojack).
